function (bytes32) view external returns (contract IERC20[] memory,uint256[] memory,uint256)

deposit(address,uint256[],address[],uint.details: Deposits tokens in the given pool. Creates new Farm contract if there isn't one deployed for the {lpPool} and deposits tokens in it.

params.amountLP: - Additional amount of LP tokens to deposit.
params.lpPool: - Address of the pool to deposit tokens in.
params.minAmountLP: - Minimum LP the user will receive from {{tokens}} deposit.
params.recipient: - Address which will recieve the deposit.

returns.liquidity: - Total liquidity sent to the farm (in lpTokens).

distribute(address,(bytes32,uint256,uint.details: Distributes tokens between users for a single {Farms[lpPool]}.

params.assets: - The data used to swap reward tokens for the needed tokens.
params.limits: - The data used to swap reward tokens for the needed tokens. Note: This function can only be called by the distributor.
params.swaps: - The data used to swap reward tokens for the needed tokens.

params.lpPool: - LP pool to check tokens in.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate that the this implementation remains valid after an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

totalDeposits(address).details: Returns total amount locked in the pool. Doesn't take pending rewards into account.

params.lpPool: - LP pool to check total deposits in.

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

userStake(address,address).details: Returns LP tokens staked by the {_address} for the given {lpPool}.

params._address: - The address to check stakes for.
params.lpPool: - LP pool to check stakes in.

withdraw(address,uint256,uint256[],bool,.details: Withdraws tokens from the given pool.

params.minAmountsOut: - Minimum token amounts the user will recieve.
params.recipient: - The address which will recieve tokens.
params.withdrawLP: - True: Withdraw in LP tokens, False: Withdraw in normal tokens.

farmFactory.details: Contract Variables: farmFactory - The contract that deploys new Farms and links them to {lpPool}s. accessManager - Role manager contract.
